JUNE 4 - 10, 2021

This photo gallery highlights some of the most compelling images made or published in the past week by The Associated Press from the North American region.

The selection was curated by AP photo editor Courtney Dittmar in New York.

story_text: AP Week in Pictures: North America AP Week in Pictures: North America. . The Associated Press . June 11, 2021 Updated: June 11, 2021 1:07 a.m. . . 1 of 20 Emely, left, is reunited with her mother, Glenda Valdez and sister, Zuri, at Austin-Bergstrom International Airport, Sunday, June 6, 2021, in Austin, Texas. It had been six years since Valdez said goodbye to her daughter Emely in Honduras. Then, last month, she caught a glimpse of a televised Associated Press photo of a little girl in a red hoodie and knew that Emely had made the trip alone into the United States. On Sunday, the child was returned to her mother's custody. Eric Gay/AP Show More Show Less 2 of 20 Crowds gather on L Street Beach, Saturday, June 5, 2021, in the South Boston neighborhood of Boston. New England is giving the rest of the country a possible glimpse into the future if more Americans get vaccinated. The six-state region has among the highest vaccination rates in the U.S. and is seeing sustained drops in COVID-19 cases, hospitalizations and deaths. Michael Dwyer/AP Show More Show Less 3 of 20 4 of 20 Logan Paul, left, and Floyd Mayweather fight during an exhibition boxing match at Hard Rock Stadium, Sunday, June 6, 2021, in Miami Gardens, Fla. Lynne Sladky/AP Show More Show Less 5 of 20 Community members gather in George Floyd Square to demand justice for Winston Boogie Smith Jr., on Monday, June 7, 2021. Smith was shot by members of a U.S. Marshals task force. Christian Monterrosa/AP Show More Show Less 6 of 20 7 of 20 An annular solar eclipse rises over the skyline of Toronto on Thursday, June 10, 2021. (Frank Gunn/The Canadian Press via AP) Frank Gunn/AP Show More Show Less 8 of 20 Melodi Butler, 6, stands on a stoop beside a makeshift memorial at the scene where 10-year old Justin Wallace was shot and killed the previous Saturday night in the Rockaway section of the Queens borough of New York, Wednesday, June 9, 2021. Police arrested Jovan Young on Tuesday in connection with the death. Young, 29, is facing charges including murder, attempted murder and assault. John Minchillo/AP Show More Show Less 9 of 20 10 of 20 A Haitian migrant family looks to emerge from a rocky canal adjacent to a gap in the U.S. border wall in Yuma, Ariz., Wednesday, June 9, 2021. Eugene Garcia/AP Show More Show Less 11 of 20 Projections of selected works of celebrated painter Vincent Van Gogh are displayed at a preview of the Immersive Van Gogh exhibit at Pier 36, Friday, June 4, 2021, in New York. John Minchillo/AP Show More Show Less 12 of 20 13 of 20 People walk through a new addition to the Las Vegas Convention Center during the World of Concrete convention Tuesday, June 8, 2021, in Las Vegas. John Locher/AP Show More Show Less 14 of 20 Protesters clash with police early Saturday, June 5, 2021, in Minneapolis, after a vigil was held for Winston Boogie Smith Jr., a Black man who was fatally shot by members of a U.S. Marshals task force. Christian Monterrosa/AP Show More Show Less 15 of 20 16 of 20 With face masks off and big smiles, the class of 2021 celebrates at the close of the Monument Mountain Regional High School graduation ceremony at the school in Great Barrington, Mass., Saturday, June 5, 2021. (Stephanie Zollshan/The Berkshire Eagle via AP) Stephanie Zollshan/AP Show More Show Less 17 of 20 A woman rides her bike past a goose as the sun sets, Wednesday, June 9, 2021, in Overland Park, Kan. Charlie Riedel/AP Show More Show Less 18 of 20 19 of 20 Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer of N.Y., talks with reporters on Capitol Hill in Washington, Tuesday, June 8, 2021.
